      • parsePointsFromFile

        public MyArrayList<Point> parsePointsFromFile(String csvSeparator,
                                              int xCoord,
                                              int yCoord,
                                              int zValue)
        Reads rows from given csv (must set with constructor or setFileName(java.lang.String)) file and parses MyArrayList of Point objects from values. Csv file must have column names on first row, other columns are ignored.
        Parameters:
        csvSeparator - Separator used in csv file (usually ";" )
        xCoord - column name for X-coordinate
        yCoord - column name for Y-coordinate
        zValue - column name for value to interpolate, the weight or Z-coordinate of point.
        Returns:
        MyArrayList of parsed Point or null if invalid file

      • getCsvHeaders

        public String[] getCsvHeaders(String csvSeparator)
        Returns an array of headers in given csv file. That is the first line of file, splited by given separator.
        Parameters:
        csvSeparator - csv separator to use in split
        Returns:
        an array of headers, null if invalid file
